Package: lpjreadr
Type: Package
Title: lpjreadr provides a quick and easy way to extract data from LPJ-GUESS smartoutput files
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Ben", "Meyer", email = "meyer.ben93@gmail.com",
  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: lpjreadr provides functions which make it easier to deal with output data from the
    smartouput module of LPJ-GUESS which is stored in netcdf format. lpjreadr handles the extraction
    of multiple variables at once and outputs them in tidy, nested tibbles.
License: AGPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    glue,
    dplyr,
    stringr,
    ncdf4,
    purrr,
    tibble,
    utils,
    matrixStats,
    vctrs
RoxygenNote: 7.2.1
